Definition.WordDefinition:
maxwell \maxwell\ n. A cgs unit of magnetic flux, abbreviated Mx; it is equal to the magnetic flux passing through one sqaure centimeter which is normal to a magnetic field of one gauss.
Syn: Mx. [WordNet 1.5 +PJC]

maxwell n 1: a cgs unit of magnetic flux equal to the flux perpendicular to an area of 1 square centimeter in a magnetic field of 1 gauss [syn: {Mx}] 2: Scottish physicist whose equations unified electricity and magnetism and who recognized the electromagnetic nature of light (1831-1879) [syn: {J. C. Maxwell}, {James Clerk Maxwell}]
